Body:
And if We cause him to taste grace after some misfortune that had
			befallen him, he saith: The ills have gone from me. Lo! he is
			exultant, boastful;

And he was building the ship, and every time that chieftains of
			his people passed him, they made mock of him. He said: Though ye
			make mock of us, yet we mock at you even as ye mock;
